----

Game publishers are affected by software patents in multiple ways.  In particular the development of 3D libraries is said to have been hampered by patents for a long time, even before some recent spectacular lawsuits erupted.  Some game makers and their associations have protested against software patents. 

== News & Chronology ==

 * 2004-11-17 US [http://news.com.com/Patent+suits+target+games+industry/2100-1030_3-5456632.html CNET (Festa): Patent suits target game industry] 
 * 2004-11-17 US [http://news.zdnet.com/2100-9588_22-5456632.html ZDNet.com: Patent suits target games industry]
 * 2004-11-05 US [http://www.theregister.co.uk/2004/11/05/graphics_patent_suit_update/ The Register: Graphics patent holder sues Sony, MS, Nintendo]
 * 2004-11-04 US [http://www.theregister.co.uk/2004/11/04/mckool_smith_lawsuit_update/ The Register: 3D patent suit extended to Dell, HP, IBM, Sony, others]
 * 2004-11-02 US [http://biz.gamedaily.com/features.asp?article_id=8236Â§ion=feature&email= GameDailyBiz: Multi-Publisher Legal War Looms Over 3-D Patent] ([http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=04/11/02/1724231 Slashdot discussion])
 * 2004-07-28 US [:Creative040728En: Creative pressures ID (Doom 3) with shadow calculation patent]
 * 2004-05-xx FR French Computer Game Association [http://www.apom.fr/ APOM] publishes position for Parliament, against Council

== Outline ==

 * game publishers are affected by software patents in multiple ways
 * in particular the development of 3D libraries is said to have been hampered by patents
 * some game makers and their associations have protested against software patents 
